    <h1>SCHOOL DAZE</h1>
    <h2></h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20201130/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-11-30"><time>2020-11-30</time></a>
        - <span>LIFE</span>
        - <span role="byline">Elisa Chia Cor&#xAD;re&#xAD;spon&#xAD;dent</span>
    </section>

    <p>Ed­u­ca­tion Min­is­ter Lawrence Wong sur­prised quite a few peo­ple when he re­vealed that he went to Tan­jong Ka­tong Sec­ondary Tech­ni­cal School.</p>
    <p>In a re­cent Straits Times in­ter­view with ex­ec­u­tive ed­i­tor Su­miko Tan, he said: “Some­times, some peo­ple will ask me, strangely, ‘You know, why didn’t you go to other schools?’</p>
    <p>“But why? It was very nat­u­ral to con­tinue my ed­u­ca­tion in a school that was near to home and where all my friends were, and I en­joyed my­self tremen­dously.”</p>
    <p>This year’s el­i­gi­ble Pri­mary 6 pupils have till to­mor­row to sub­mit their sec­ondary school choices af­ter re­ceiv­ing their Pri­mary School Leav­ing Ex­am­i­na­tion re­sults.</p>
    <p>With se­lec­tion fever go­ing on, ST turns the spotlight on six per­son­al­i­ties and their sec­ondary school mem­o­ries.</p>
    <p>elisac@sph.com.sg</p>


